⊕meta⊕
name = "find-unused-sky-workflows"
description = "Cross-reference every .sky in a dir against sky run history; list never-run / long-stale files as advisory deletion candidates. Prints ready-to-paste delete commands but deletes nothing."
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

§list§
bash = "set -eu\nDIR=\"$SKY_DIR\"\nif [ -z \"$DIR\" ]; then echo 'ERROR: --var dir is required' >&2; exit 1; fi\nif [ ! -d \"$DIR\" ]; then echo \"ERROR: not a directory: $DIR\" >&2; exit 1; fi\nFOUND=0\nfor f in \"$DIR\"/*.sky; do\n  [ -e \"$f\" ] || continue\n  b=\"$(basename \"$f\" .sky)\"\n  echo \"$b\"\n  FOUND=$((FOUND + 1))\ndone\nif [ \"$FOUND\" -eq 0 ]; then echo \"ERROR: no .sky files in $DIR\" >&2; exit 1; fi\necho \"---\" >&2\necho \"listed $FOUND workflow file(s) in $DIR\" >&2"
§§

§runs§
depends_on = ["list"]
bash = "set -u\nLOG=\"$(mktemp /tmp/sky-runlog.XXXXXX)\"\n# 'sky logs' format is not contractually stable; capture defensively and never let a nonzero exit kill discovery.\nif ! sky logs > \"$LOG\" 2>/dev/null; then\n  echo 'WARN: sky logs returned nonzero or is unavailable; treating history as empty' >&2\n  : > \"$LOG\"\nfi\nLINES=\"$(wc -l < \"$LOG\" | tr -d ' ')\"\nif [ \"$LINES\" = \"0\" ]; then\n  echo 'WARN: no run history parsed; every workflow will be reported as NEVER (advisory only)' >&2\nfi\ncat \"$LOG\"\nrm \"$LOG\"\necho \"---\" >&2\necho \"captured $LINES line(s) of run history\" >&2"
§§

§report§
depends_on = ["list", "runs"]
bash = "set -u\nDIR=\"$SKY_DIR\"\nFILES=\"$SKY_OUTPUT_LIST\"\nHISTORY=\"$SKY_OUTPUT_RUNS\"\nHIST_LC=\"$(printf '%s' \"$HISTORY\" | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')\"\nNEVER=0\nSEEN=0\necho '# find-unused-sky-workflows report'\necho \"# dir: $DIR\"\necho '# status legend: SEEN-IN-LOGS = name appears in sky logs; NEVER = name absent from sky logs'\necho '# NOTE advisory only: NEVER depends on log retention and on workflow name == filename. Nothing is deleted.'\necho '---'\nprintf '%s\\n' \"$FILES\" | while IFS= read -r name; do\n  [ -n \"$name\" ] || continue\n  needle=\"$(printf '%s' \"$name\" | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')\"\n  if printf '%s' \"$HIST_LC\" | grep -F -q -- \"$needle\"; then\n    echo \"SEEN-IN-LOGS   $name\"\n  else\n    echo \"NEVER          $name\"\n    echo \"  candidate: sky run delete-sky-workflow --var dir=\\\"$DIR\\\" --var name=$name\"\n  fi\ndone\necho '---'\n# Recompute counts in the parent shell (the while-loop ran in a subshell via the pipe).\nfor name in $FILES; do\n  [ -n \"$name\" ] || continue\n  needle=\"$(printf '%s' \"$name\" | tr '[:upper:]' '[:lower:]')\"\n  if printf '%s' \"$HIST_LC\" | grep -F -q -- \"$needle\"; then\n    SEEN=$((SEEN + 1))\n  else\n    NEVER=$((NEVER + 1))\n  fi\ndone\necho \"summary: $SEEN seen-in-logs, $NEVER never-run candidate(s)\"\necho 'discovery only; exit 0 regardless of findings'\nexit 0"
§§

※※
find-unused-sky-workflows — advisory dead-workflow scanner (pure bash, no Claude, no cost)

WHAT IT DOES
  Lists every <name>.sky in --var dir, cross-references each basename against
  the output of `sky logs`, and classifies it:
    SEEN-IN-LOGS  name appears (case-insensitively) somewhere in run history
    NEVER         name does NOT appear in run history -> deletion CANDIDATE
  For every NEVER file it prints a ready-to-paste command line:
    sky run delete-sky-workflow --var dir="<dir>" --var name=<name>
  It deletes NOTHING. Always exits 0 — this is discovery, not enforcement.

HONESTY / CAVEATS (read before acting on output)
  - "NEVER" is ADVISORY. It only means the name was not found in `sky logs`.
  - It is wrong if log retention has aged the run out, or if the workflow's
    `name = "..."` in ⊕meta⊕ differs from its filename (matching is by
    filename basename appearing in the log text).
  - `sky logs` output format is not a stable contract; this scan greps the raw
    text case-insensitively and tolerates an empty/unavailable log (then every
    file reports NEVER). Verify before deleting anything.
  - Recently-created-but-never-run files will also show NEVER. That is correct
    but may be intentional. Human judgment required.

DAG
  list ──► runs ──► report
   │                 ▲
   └─────────────────┘
  list   bash: print basename of each "$SKY_DIR"/*.sky (one per line); errors if dir empty/missing
  runs   bash: capture `sky logs` into a /tmp mktemp file, print it, rm the file; never fails the run
  report bash: for each file mark SEEN-IN-LOGS / NEVER; print delete suggestions; exit 0 always

RUN
  sky run find-unused-sky-workflows --var dir=/abs/path/to/.sky/workflows

VARS
  dir   (required)  Absolute path to a directory containing .sky files. -> $SKY_DIR
※※
